---
/**
 * rest-api · 0008 · Figure 4 — "header . payload . signature" (JWT structure +
 * stateless verify).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson. References the source's shared #arwG
 * arrow marker, inlined here in this figure's own <defs> with the same id/fill so
 * the component is self-contained. See Fig1.astro for the rationale.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 226"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A JWT is header dot payload dot signature; the server recomputes the signature over header and payload with its key to verify"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">header . payload . signature</text
            >
            <rect x="10" y="30" width="190" height="86" rx="9" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="105"
                y="49"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">HEADER</text
            >
            <text x="105" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >alg (e.g. RS256)</text
            >
            <text x="105" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">typ: JWT</text>
            <text x="105" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#9a2417"
                >pin alg · reject alg:none</text
            >
            <text
                x="206"
                y="78"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="16"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">.</text
            >
            <rect x="218" y="30" width="200" height="86" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#6b675f"
            ></rect>
            <text x="318" y="49" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700"
                >PAYLOAD (claims)</text
            >
            <text x="318" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >sub · iss · aud · exp</text
            >
            <text x="318" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >scopes / roles</text
            >
            <text x="318" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#9a2417"
                >base64, NOT encrypted — no secrets</text
            >
            <text
                x="424"
                y="78"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="16"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">.</text
            >
            <rect x="436" y="30" width="194" height="86" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="533"
                y="49"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">SIGNATURE</text
            >
            <text x="533" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >sign(header.payload,</text
            >
            <text x="533" y="81" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >key) → integrity</text
            >
            <text x="533" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#244a2e"
                >proves it wasn't forged</text
            >
            <!-- verify row -->
            <rect
                x="120"
                y="142"
                width="400"
                height="40"
                rx="9"
                fill="#fff"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="160"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">VERIFY: recompute sig over header+payload with the key —</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="174" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >match? then check iss, aud, exp. No match → reject.</text
            >
            <line x1="105" y1="116" x2="240" y2="142" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="318" y1="116" x2="318" y2="142" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="533" y1="116" x2="400" y2="142" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <text x="320" y="208" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >Catch: hard to revoke before exp — a JWT you don't fully validate is just
                attacker-supplied JSON.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        <code>header.payload.signature</code>, signed and verified statelessly by any node. The
        payload is base64, not encrypted, so never put secrets in it; and it is hard to revoke
        before <code>exp</code>.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
